article.headline: UTEP 79, Arkansas-Pine Bluff 51
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Maurice Thomas led Texas-El Paso with 20 points and nine rebounds as the Miners beat Arkansas-Pine Bluff 79-51 Wednesday night. UTEP (5-4) led for the entire contest, pushing the margin to a game-high 34 points with 3:33 left in the second half. Kevin Henderson came off the bench to add 15 points on 6-of-7 field goal shooting. Stefon Jackson added 13 and Darren Clarke had 11. Arkansas-Pine Bluff (2-7) was led by Jason Frierson, the team's only player to score in double digits. Tyree Glass and William Byrd had seven rebounds each. UTEP led 53-25 at the half. The Miners shot 54 percent in the first half, but dropped to 32 percent in the second half. The Golden Lions shot only 32 percent for the game. UTEP dominated in the paint, scoring 44 points inside compared to 16 for the Golden Lions.
